	<!-- message -->
	<p>I've got that too, under <a href="http://www.eqtraders.com/prices/alchemy.htm" target="_blank">Alchemy Prices</a>...it's linked off of the Learn Alchemy page, just didn't mention it above. <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt="" title="smile" smilieid="1" />  It's even sorted by trivial, for just the sort of use that you propose.  Right now I'm trying to figure out how best to indicate which potion line a given potion belongs to, to help people more quickly find the recipe since they are sorted primarily by potion line (Old Alchemy, Revamp Alchemy, Gypsy Alchemy, or Luclin Alchemy).<br />
<br />
There were only two big things that I deliberately removed from Belgar's wealth of information.  The pricing guide was replaced by a brief explanation of alchemy pricing customs in the FAQ.  The loose herb cross-reference would have been too big and relatively not very useful with the new strains of herbs with Luclin muddying the waters.  Other than that, I no longer have pictures up for of each of the herbs, but everything else is there in some form or another.  Only four months later! <img src="images/smilies/rolleyes.gif" border="0" alt="" title="roll eyes (sarcastic)" smilieid="8" /></p>
	
	
	
